#compdef wasmedgec
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# WasmEdge/WasmEdge tools/wasmedge/wasmedgec.cpp entrypoint +
# include/driver/compiler.h `DriverCompilerOptions` struct +
# lib/driver/compilerTool.cpp `Parser.add_option(...)` calls.
# wasmedgec is built as a separate executable per
# tools/wasmedge/CMakeLists.txt
# `wasmedge_add_executable(wasmedgec)`. The shared base options
# come from `DriverProposalOptions` (WebAssembly proposal feature
# toggles) extended with `DriverCompilerOptions` (AOT-compiler-
# specific options).
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# WasmEdge wasmedgec R150c — Ahead-Of-Time (AOT) compiler for the
# WasmEdge WebAssembly runtime. Compiles a .wasm module into a
# native .so/.dylib/.dll shared library that wasmedge can load
# at runtime for faster startup + execution. Sister to the
# heavily-covered wasmedge / wasmer / wasmtime / wac / wkg / wasm-
# tools / wit-bindgen family in the corpus.

_arguments -s -S \
  '--optimize=[optimization level (default 2)]:level:(0 1 2 3 s z)' \
  '--generic-binary[generate a generic (non-host-specific) binary]' \
  '--dump-ir[dump LLVM IR to wasm.ll and wasm-opt.ll]' \
  '--interruptible[generate an interruptible binary]' \
  '--enable-instruction-counting[emit code for counting executed Wasm instructions]' \
  '--enable-gas-measuring[emit code for counting gas burned during execution]' \
  '--enable-time-measuring[emit code for measuring execution time]' \
  '--enable-all-statistics[emit code for ALL statistics (counting + gas + time)]' \
  '--proposal=[enable a WebAssembly proposal feature]:proposal:(import-export-mut-globals nontrap-converts sign-extension-operators multi-value bulk-memory simd reference-types tail-call extended-const threads relaxed-simd function-references gc multi-memories memory64 component-model exception-handling)' \
  '--enable-all-proposals[enable all known WebAssembly proposals]' \
  '1:input WebAssembly file:_files -g "*.(wasm|wat)"' \
  '2:output shared-library file:_files -g "*.(so|dylib|dll)"'
